{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01K1xX5i7D7ZeqwjFtTfvmWP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So there's already a `log4j2.file.properties` that writes JSON logs to files! ES uses this when the system property `-Des.logs.style=file` is set. I need to check how to enable it.\n\nActually, in ES 8.x, if you set the environment variable `ES_LOG_STYLE=file`, it uses `log4j2.file.properties` instead of `log4j2.properties`. That would write JSON logs to files.\n\nWait, let me check the ES 8.x documentation. In ES 8.x Docker images, the startup script checks for `ES_LOG_STYLE` and uses either `log4j2.properties` (console/stdout) or `log4j2.file.properties` (file-based).\nThe file-based configuration writes JSON logs to a specific path under the logs directory, which defaults to `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs`. If I set `ES_LOG_STYLE=file` in the container environment, Filebeat can then read those JSON logs from a shared volume mounted at that path. I'm thinking through how to wire this together with ConfigMaps and volumes in Kubernetes.\n\nI need to patch the StatefulSet to add the environment variable, create an emptyDir volume for logs, and mount it at the logs path in the Elasticsearch container. Then both Metricbeat and Filebeat sidecars can access their respective configurations and the shared logs volume. Let me verify whether there's already an explicit mount for the logs directory that I'd be replacing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1683,"cache_read_input_tokens":37145,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1683},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"262bb4ad-adb6-41a1-8918-e63b58536b56","uuid":"794627ea-516f-49f0-9b98-fa153be